## Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

### Scope: one file, two additions — `common/chat.cpp`

No changes to `src/llama-chat.h`, `src/llama-chat.cpp`, or any existing handler.

---

### Background

llama.cpp has two template layers. The **modern Jinja layer** (`common/chat.cpp`) has a specialized-handler dispatcher: `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`. It checks the raw Jinja source string and, when a template matches a known shape, hands off to a dedicated C++ function instead of the generic autoparser.

The existing Ministral 3 check (lines 1640–1644) fires when the source contains **`[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`**. Mistral Instruct v0.3 uses `[INST]/[/INST]` but never `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`, so it currently falls through. The new handler fills that gap.

---

### Step 1 — New handler function (insert after line 940, before `common_chat_params_init_gpt_oss`)

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
    const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
    const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 format:
    //   [INST] {optional system\n\n}{user} [/INST] {assistant}</s> [INST] {user} [/INST] …
    // System messages are prepended inside the opening [INST] block of the first user turn.
    common_chat_params data;
    std::string prompt;
    bool is_inside_turn = false;

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        const auto role = msg.value("role", "");
        std::string content;
        if (msg.contains("content") && msg.at("content").is_string()) {
            content = msg.at("content").get<std::string>();
        }

        if (role == "system") {
            if (!is_inside_turn) {
                prompt += "[INST] ";
                is_inside_turn = true;
            }
            prompt += content + "\n\n";
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (!is_inside_turn) {
                prompt += "[INST] ";
                is_inside_turn = true;
            }
            prompt += content + " [/INST]";
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
            is_inside_turn = false;
        }
    }

    data.prompt = std::move(prompt);
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

Key choices:
- `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` — no grammar/PEG parser needed for this simple format.
- Mirrors the logic in the legacy `MISTRAL_V3` handler (`llama-chat.cpp` lines 267–291): system is absorbed inside the opening `[INST]` of the first turn.
- Prompt naturally ends with ` [/INST]` after the last user message — the correct inference boundary; no explicit generation-prompt suffix needed.

