### Step 2 — Detection block (insert after line 1644, inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`)

```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
// Distinguishes from the Ministral/Magistral Large 3 handler above (which requires [SYSTEM_PROMPT]).
if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
    LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
    return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
}
```

- `[INST]` present → Mistral-family marker.
- `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absent → cannot be Ministral 3 or V7/V7-Tekken.
- Placed **after** the Ministral 3 block, so the more-specific handler (which needs `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`) always wins first.

---

### Expected output

`system="Be helpful"`, `user="Hello"`, `assistant="Hi"`, `user="Bye"` →
```
[INST] Be helpful\n\nHello [/INST] Hi</s>[INST] Bye [/INST]
```

